data.description:
The text to be checked, provided as a JSON document that specifies text and markup. Either this field or 'text' is mandatory. Markup is disregarded when identifying errors. Example text: <pre>A &lt;b>test&lt;/b></pre>JSON for the example text: <pre>{"annotation":[
 {"text": "A "},
 {"markup": "&lt;b>"},
 {"text": "test"},
 {"markup": "&lt;/b>"}
]}</pre> <p>If there is markup to be treated as whitespace, such as <tt>&lt;p&gt;</tt> in HTML, it can be interpreted as follows: <pre>{"markup": "&lt;p&gt;", "interpretAs": "\n\n"}</pre><p>The 'data' functionality is not restricted to HTML or XML; it is applicable to any markup.
